Mark and Trina were there when it happened. They survived. But now a virus is spreading. A virus that fills humans with murderous rage.

They’re convinced that there’s a way to save those who are left—if they can stay alive. Because in this new, devastated world, every life has a price. And to some you’re worth more dead than alive.', 'In a world scorched by sun flares, survivors Mark and Trina battle a deadly virus that drives people into murderous frenzy, seeking a cure amid chaos and betrayal.', 2012, '0385742894', '9780307979117', 384, NULL, 598, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/9056187-L.jpg', '/works/OL16671713W', NULL, '2012', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'the-kill-order-james-dashner', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:44:20', '2026-03-22 20:32:05');
